    <text>
        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(center)"><placeName>Kingston Jamaica</placeName> <date>7<hi rend="sup">th</hi> May 5609</date>.</p>
			<p>My dear Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">I avail myself of the present opportunity<lb/> to acknowledge the receipt of your communication&#44; and<lb/> at the same time&#44; to express my warm thanks for the kind<lb/> sentiments which it breathes. Being aware how deeply at<lb/> heart&#44; I have the subject of our correspondence you need no<lb/> assurance on my part&#44; how earnestly I have taken into<lb/> consideration the contents of your esteemed letter. I readily<lb/> admit the desirability of being on the spot&#44; wherever a situation<lb/> should offer&#59; but as you <add>&#63;</add> second my situation&#59; I shall<lb/> briefly and openly place you in possession of my position. The<lb/> proceeds of my labor are far from being unremunerative&#44; but<lb/> having a family to maintain&#44; I could ill spare the<lb/> expense of <sic>travelling</sic>&#44; without the matter being definitely<lb/> settled before hand. I have no doubt of being able to<lb/> obtain leave of absence from the Directors of the Hebrew National<lb/> Institution&#44; yet&#44; this would but partly be of service&#44; for I would&#44;<lb/> of necessity&#44; have to relinquish many <hi rend="underline">private</hi> pupils&#44; the<lb/> emoluments arising from whom are about &#36;200 pr ann. This<lb/> is the sole reason which renders my repairing so <placeName><sic>Cincinatti</sic></placeName>&#44; im&#61;<lb/>&#61;practicable&#44; otherwise&#44; I would not fear the result. The fame<lb/> remarks apply to any other situation&#44; if my election be left to<lb/> chance. I do not however&#44; relinquish the hope of obtaining<lb/> a clerical situation in the <placeName>United States</placeName>&#44; as I can &#40;if required&#41;<lb/> procure testimonials of the most satisfactory nature.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Since my last communication&#44; I</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>have been elected <add>Hebrew</add> of the congregation <add>Hebrew</add> of <placeName>Spanish town</placeName>&#44;<lb/> so that I am de facto as this moment&#44; one of the Jewish Clergy.<lb/> I think it necessary&#44; However to premise&#44; that an understanding<lb/> exists that I am thereby unfettered in accepting any other<lb/> ministerial office. My object in responding to their call<lb/> has been solely with the view of reorganizing the Congregation<lb/> which&#44; in a religious sense&#44; has ceased to exist. The community<lb/> are not in a position to compensate a minister&#44; I am therefore<lb/> compelled to retain my situation as master of the school in<lb/> <placeName>Kingston</placeName>&#44; and on occasions of Service&#44; go to the <placeName>Spanish Town</placeName> by the<lb/> Train the afternoon previous. You will therefore not fail to<lb/> perceive that in this matter I have not been influenced by<lb/> pecuniary gain. In what I have done&#44; I have been actuated<lb/> merely by a desire to promote the cause of our Holy Religion&#44;<lb/> and to remove the stigma from a body of Israelites&#44; having<lb/> <hi rend="underline">two</hi> places of Worship&#44; and neither open for the service of the God<lb/> of <persName>Jacob</persName>. So far have I been successful. The taunting question<lb/> can no longer be uttered&#63; <add>Hebrew</add>. Under my superintendence<lb/> a Sunday School is also about being established&#44; as with scarcely<lb/> an exception the younger branches of the community are ignorant of<lb/> the very first principles of our faith&#44; much less of our national<lb/> Language. Thro&#39; the instruction I have received from Hazan <persName>Lopes</persName><lb/> of our city &#40;of whom you have perhaps heard&#41; I am enabled to<lb/> officiate in the Portuguese Minhag&#44; but I should&#44; nevertheless&#44; prefer<lb/> being attached as Minister to a German Congregation &#40;<add>Hebrew</add>&#41; in the<lb/> <placeName>United States</placeName>&#44; having had much more experience&#44; and being<lb/> <hi rend="underline">perfectly</hi> an fait at the duties of the latter. I therefore&#44; <hi rend="underline">do not</hi><lb/> relinquish the desire of obtaining a situation as Hazan in <placeName>America</placeName>.<lb/> May I rely on your continued good offices in forwarding my</p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p>views&#63; In contending <add>&#63;</add><lb/> think me unmindful <add>&#63;</add><lb/> you have manifested towa<add>&#63;</add><lb/> <hi rend="underline">immediate</hi> opportunity of <add>&#63;</add><lb/> works&#44; but should the <add>&#63;</add><lb/> in proving how fully <add>&#63;</add><lb/> me</p>
			<p>they are indeed well <add>&#63;</add><lb/> well as the mechanic<add>&#63;</add><lb/> <hi rend="underline">as yet</hi> in procuring any<add>&#63;</add><lb/> many whose <hi rend="underline">names</hi> I could <add>&#63;</add><lb/> your losses in this report&#44; <add>&#63;</add><lb/> however despair of obtain<add>&#63;</add><lb/> placed&#44; in fact&#44; who wou<add>&#63;</add><lb/> At Present&#44; there is better<add>&#63;</add><lb/> here. The Directors <add>&#63;</add><lb/> Institution&#41; are <persName>P Lan<add>&#63;</add></persName><lb/> <persName>Alex</persName>. <persName>Aria Freas</persName>&#8212;L<add>&#63;</add><lb/> <persName>L Alexander</persName>&#44; <persName>D May<add>&#63;</add></persName><lb/> <persName>Abm Bravo</persName>&#44; &#38; <persName>M B He<add>&#63;</add></persName></p>
			<p>Town&#44; are <persName>Abm. Judah</persName> Pre<add>&#63;</add><lb/> <persName>Elias Sangueretti</persName>&#44; <persName>George Ab<add>&#63;</add></persName><lb/> <persName>Melhado</persName> Hon Sec&#44; &#38; <persName>D D Soa<add>&#63;</add></persName><lb/> in the 1<hi rend="sup">st</hi> night of <date>Passover</date>&#44;<add>&#63;</add><lb/> it not for the postage&#44; I wo<add>&#63;</add><lb/> on malaihe<add>&#63;</add> 2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> &#40;<add>Hebrew</add>&#41;<add>&#63;</add><lb/> will avail myself of the op<add>&#63;</add></p>
			<p>remembered to you&#44; and so<add>&#63;</add><lb/> the assurance of my respect<add>&#63;</add><lb/> B<add>&#63;</add></p>
          
